      "raw_text": "A. A. Persinger, railway clerk on\nthe Great Northern. returning from\nSeattle Saturday night. tells of the\nwreck near Wellington. causing IL\nhours delay. The two front engines\nand baggage car had about passed\nthe tunnel when they ran into\nswitch and were derailed, leaving the\nremainder of the train on the track\n\n\nThe two engines and baggage car\nran onto the trestle bridge. the en-\ngines making 1t safely. but the bag\ngage car went through into the ditch,\nsmashing 1t to atoms. No one was in\nthe car at the time. The contents\nconsisting OF large amount of fish,\nwere made into mince meat. A"
    }
  ]
